Task1
1. Create a database-server namespace <file> 
2. Run mariadb inside it <file> 
3. Expose the database into a service <file>
4. Access the service from a mysql client <command> fromdatabase-client namespace (create the namespace)
5. k apply -f <filename>

Note 
when you access the database -h option give it servicename.namespace


Namespace database-server 

1. pod => mariadb-server, service x 
2. pod => mysql-client 

Action  pod2 access pod1 using the service name. command = mysql -u root -p1234 -h x.database-server.svc.cluster.local



1. pod => mariadb-server, namespace database-server    x.database-server.cluster.local
2. pod => mysql-client, namespace database-client  
Action pod2 access pod1 using the service name.  command = mysql -u root -p1234 -h x.database-client.svc.cluster.local




kubectl -n <namspace> 
kubecto config --help
